  "text": "For networks I, C, and A, we use the same VGG network [CITATION_1] structure. Meanwhile, I and C share parameters in the training stage to speed up convergence. For network G, it is an inverse VGG structure. Its pooling layers are replaced by upsampling layers, and the convolution layers are replaced with deconvolution layers. For network D, we use the same discriminative network structure as the DCGAN [CITATION_2] . The batch normalization [CITATION_3] layer is also applied after each convolution and deconvolution layer. The model is implemented using the deep learning toolbox Torch.",
